[src:kubernetes-pod-security/role-based-access-control] Permission authorization: A subject can exercise a permission only if the permission is authorized for the subject's active role.
[src:kubernetes-pod-security/role-based-access-control] With rules 1 and 2, this rule ensures that users can exercise only permissions for which they are authorized.
[src:kubernetes-pod-security/role-based-access-control] Additional constraints may be applied as well, and roles can be combined in a hierarchy where higher-level roles subsume permissions owned by sub-roles.
